column2: Using externally controlled strings in a command line may allow a malicious user to change the meaning of the command.
An HTTP request handler that performs expensive operations without restricting the rate at which operations can be carried out is vulnerable to denial-of-service attacks.
column4: This route handler performs [["a system command"|"relative:///lib/api/index.js:76:7:89:8"]], but is not rate-limited.
